Set exception output message log level from **DEBUG** to **WARN** When sending data to kafka error occurred,because in production environment log level usually be info or higher level,debug level error message is invisible and we don't know lost data when send data to kafka.

`  
 if (exception != null) {
      logger.warn("Error sending message to Kafka {} ", exception.getMessage());
    }
`

When using memory-channel, the header is retrieved from sink and the metadata information of Kafka is retrieved from it, but when using kafka-channel, it is not retrieved

```
HDFSEventSink.class
public Status process() throws EventDeliveryException{
.....
Channel channel = getChannel();
Event event = channel.take();
Map<String, String> headers = event.getHeaders();
String topic = headers.get("topic");
String key = headers.get("key");
String offset = headers.get("offset");
System.out.println("topic = " + topic);
System.out.println("key = " + key);
System.out.println("offset = " + offset);
}
```


In the above code, the printed value is empty, so this solves the problem
